<chapter xml:id="ch-Functions" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" component="QEG">
    <title>MA130 Functions</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
        MA130 gives students the preparation they need to 
        succeed in calculus and to apply their knowledge 
        of algebraic and transcendental functions to other 
        fields of study. Linear, exponential, logarithmic, 
        trigonometric, polynomial, rational, and 
        piecewise-defined functions are examined from 
        symbolic, graphical, numerical, and verbal points of 
        view. 
    </p>
  </introduction>
    <section xml:id="sec-Func-topics">
        <title>Topics in MA130 Functions</title>
        <p>
            Topics includeÂ sketching and analyzing graphs, 
            rates of change, inverses, and transformations of 
            functions. Applications to science, social science, 
            and business will be included. Students will be 
            encouraged to become more independent mathematical 
            thinkers as they solve problems. 
        </p>
        <p>
            This course is not available for credit to students who 
            have successfully completed a collegiate course equivalent to MA 165 
            or higher. On the other hand, students who took a calculus
            course in high school which focused primarily on computations
            with little attention to theory and applications 
            may benefit from MA130 and are allow to enroll.
        </p>
        <p>
            The prerequisites for MA130 are the same as the learning 
            outcomes for MA112 College Algebra,
            a course recommended only for students 
            who plan also to take MA130 Functions. In MA130, it 
            will be assumed that students can
            simplify algebraic expressions, solve linear and quadratic 
            equations, work with exponents and radicals, compute the slope
            and give an equation of a line through two points, and work with functional 
            notation prior to the start of the course. 
        </p>
        <p component="quant">
            Sample prerequisite problems may be viewed at 
            <xref ref="ch-CA" text="custom">MA112 College Algebra</xref> and 
            at the end of the current page. You are encouraged to look at these  
            problems, attempting and self-checking enough of them to determine 
            whether you are prepared for MA130 Functions.
            If most of these algebra problems in 
            <xref ref="ch-CA" text="custom">MA112 College Algebra</xref> are 
            difficult for you, you might want to begin in MA112 instead of MA130.
        </p>

