        </exercise>
        <exercise>
            <title>Work with functions defined verbally</title>
            <statement>
            <p>        
                The money in a bank account is increasing by 5% 
                every year. There is $30,000 in the account in 2020. 
            </p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        Write a formula for $A(t)$, the amount of 
                        money in the account <m>t</m> years after 2020. 
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p> 
                        Determine the amount of money in the account in 
                        2025.
                    </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p>
                        In what year will the amount of money reach $100,000?
                    </p>
                </li>   
            </ol>    
            </statement>
            <hint>
                <p>    
                    Is this function linear, exponential, or something else?
                </p>
            </hint>
            <answer>
                <p>
                (a) <m>A(t)=30000(1.05)^t</m>; (b) $38,288 exactly 5 years after it 
                had $30,000; (c) During late 2044 or approximately 25 years after 2020
                </p>
            </answer>
            <solution>
                <p>
                    (a) The growth is exponential. Each year we have the amount that was 
                    in the account the previous year plus an additional 0.05 times that 
                    amount. Thus, we are multiplying the amount in the account by $1+0.05$
                    each year giving a formula of <m>A(t)=30000(1.05)^t</m>. 
                
                    (b) <m>30000(1.05)^5\approx 32.288</m>;

                    (c) Solve <m>100000=30000(1.05)^t</m> using logarithms or by 
                    viewing where the curves of <m>y=100000</m> and <m>y=30000(1.05)^t</m> intersect 
                    on a graphing 
                    calculator or similar app. To use logarithms,
                    <md>
                        <mrow>\frac{10}{3}\amp=1.05^t </mrow>
                        <mrow>ln\left(\frac{10}{3}\right)\amp=t(ln(1.05))</mrow>
                        <mrow>\frac{ln(\frac{10}{3})}{ln(1.05)}\amp=t</mrow>
                        <mrow>t\approx 24.68</mrow>
                    </md>
                </p>
    </solution>
        </exercise>
        <exercise>
            <title>Determine the inverse of a function and use it to solve problems</title>
            <statement>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Determine the inverses of the following functions:
                        </p>
                        
                        <ol>
                            <li><m>f(x)=3x-7</m></li>
                            <li><m>g(x)=\frac{5}{x+8}</m></li>
                            <li><m>h(t)=2\ln(6t)</m></li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Use inverse properties to simplify <m>f^{-1}(f(3y))-y</m>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                        Determine the angle <m>\theta</m> such that <m>\tan\theta=-1</m> and <m>0\lt\theta\lt \pi</m>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </statement>
        </exercise>
        <exercise>
            <title>Combine and transform functions</title>
            <statement>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                            <p>
                                Let <m>f(x)=x+3</m> and <m>g(x)=2x^2-x+4</m>. Determine the following:
                            </p>
                        <ol cols="2">
                            <li>
                                <m>(f+g)(x)</m>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <m>(fg)(2)</m>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <m>g\circ f(x)</m>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
                            Describe how the graph of <m>h(x)=-2f(x)</m> is 
                            related to the graph of <m>y=f(x)</m>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </statement>
            <answer>
                <p>
                    a. i. <m>(f+g)(x)=2x^2+7</m>;
                    ii. <m>(fg)(2)=50</m>; iii. <m>f\circ g(x)=2x^2+11x+19</m>
                    b. The graph is reflected over the <m>x</m>-axis and stretched 
                    vertically by a factor of 2.
                </p>
            </answer>
            <solution>
                <p>
                <ol>
                    <li>
                      <ol>                        
                        <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>(f+g)(x)=f(x)+g(x)=(x+3)+(2x^2-x+4)=2x^2+7</m>
                        </p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>(fg)(2)=f(2)g(2)=5\cdot 10=50</m>
                        </p>
                        </li> 
                        <li>
                        <p>
                            <m>f\circ g(x)=2(x+3)^2-(x+3)+4
                            =2x^2+12x+18-x-3+4=2x^2+11x+19</m>  
                        </p>
                        </li> 
                      </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
                </p>
            </solution>
        </exercise>
