    <section xml:id="sec-functions-ready">
        <title>Are you ready for MA130?</title>
        <p component="EG">
            Some students need to reinforce their algebraic skills 
            and understanding to prepare for success in MA130. If you 
            are able to do most of the problems in the next set on your 
            own, then you should do well in MA130. If you want to eventually 
            take Functions and possibly Calculus but you 
            struggle with most of these prerequisite problems, then you 
            should begin in MA112 College Algebra. More information is available  
            in the <url 
            href="https://tjmagnus.github.io/RivRaider-math-course-selections/quantitative/ch-CA.html">
            visual="mathematics course selection document for majors in quantitative 
            fields"</url>. 
            If do not plan on taking MA130 either now or in the future, 
            we recommend that you choose <xref ref="ch-Puzzles" text="title"> or 
            <xref ref="ch-GeoEx" text="title"/>, not MA112.
        </p>
        <p component="quant">
            Some students need to reinforce their algebraic skills 
