    <section>
        <title>Choosing Your Course</title>
            <p>
              To summarize, MA130 Functions is the right course for you if 
              you are strong in algebra techniques, such as those shown in 
              <xref ref="sec-functions-ready"/>, but find many of the problems 
              in <xref ref="exer-130"/>
              to be unfamiliar or difficult. In MA130, there will also be an emphasis on 
              doing problems that are closer to how you encounter mathematics beyond the classroom; your 
              ability to take a mathematical situation and rephrase it into a formula will grow. 
              
              On the other hand, if you are very comfortable completing most of 
              the above problems on your own with only minor errors, 
              then you may be ready to enroll in <xref ref="ch-above130" 
              text="custom">MA165 Calculus 
              or a higher-level course</xref>. Select "course above MA130" on the 
              Directed Self-Placement Tool and talk to your advisor and/or 
              the mathematics program director to help you determine the right 
              course for you.
              Credit for Advanced Placement exams will be considered once scores 
              are received (see <xref ref="ch-FAQ" text="title"/>).
              </p>
              <p>
              If you are ready to confirm your mathematics course selection 
              or consider courses above MA130, return to the Directed Self-Placement and 
              check the box for the desired course of action. 
            </p>
